-- Austrian Golfer Bernd Wiesberger Wins Ballantine’s Championship
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-04-29T12:12:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-29/austrian-golfer-bernd-wiesberger-wins-ballantine-s-championship.html
Austria’s Bernd Wiesberger scored a
final-round 68, 4-under par, to win golf’s Ballantine’s
Championship by five shots today, his first European Tour title.  Wiesberger finished on 18-under-par 270 at Icheon,  South
Korea . Richie Ramsay of Scotland was second, and Victor
Dubuisson of France and Australia’s Marcus Fraser were joint
third, two shots further back.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 